<kml xmlns="http://www.opengis.net/kml/2.2" xmlns:gx="http://www.google.com/kml/ext/2.2" xmlns:kml="http://www.opengis.net/kml/2.2" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom">
<Document>
	<name>Mapping Dubliners Project</name>
	<open>1</open>
	<description><![CDATA[<p>This map is a visualization of the streets, locations, and routes depicted in James Joyce's Dubliners. Each place marker provides a brief contextual explanation and contains the passage from the text in which the reference appears.</p>

<p>Quotations are from the 1967 Modern Library edition.</p>

<p>View the <i>Dubliners</i> <a href="http://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/2814" terget="_blank">full text</a> at Project Gutenberg.]]></description>
