			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin12</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<gx:drawOrder>1</gx:drawOrder>
				<coordinates>-6.264415409926557,53.34270570787157,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Westmoreland Street</name>
			<description><![CDATA["Two Gallants"<br>[where one of Lenehan's friends says he saw Mac earlier]<br>"One said that he had seen Mac an hour before in Westmoreland Street. At 
this Lenehan said that he had been with Mac the night before in Egan's. 
The young man who had seen Mac in Westmoreland Street asked was it true 
that Mac had won a bit over a billiard match. Lenehan did not know: he 
said that Holohan had stood them drinks in Egan's" (58).<br>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin8</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.259116,53.345726,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>George&apos;s Street</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<div dir="ltr">&quot;Two Gallants&quot;<br>[where Lenehan walks after speaking to his friends]<br>&quot;He left his friends at a quarter to ten and went up George&#39;s Street. He turned to the left at the City Markets and walked on into Grafton Street&quot; (58).</div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin8</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.26446,53.34320100000001,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Ely Place</name>
			<description><![CDATA["Two Gallants"<br>[where Corley swerves off before allowing Lenehan to catch up]<br>"They had reached the corner of Ely Place" (60).<br>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin8</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.254245,53.337372,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
