	<Folder>
		<name>&quot;Counterparts&quot;</name>
		<description>Streets, Locations, and Routes in &quot;Counterparts.&quot;</description>
		<Placemark>
			<name>O&apos;Neill&apos;s</name>
			<description>[where Farrington goes to get a quick drink before finishing his copies; where he considers going to borrow money]

&quot;He was now safe in the dark snug of O&apos;Neill&apos;s
shop, and filling up the little window that looked into the bar with his
inflamed face, the colour of dark wine or dark meat, he called out:

&apos;Here, Pat, give us a g.p., like a good fellow&apos;&quot; (88)

&quot;On the stairs a moist pungent odour of
perfumes saluted his nose: evidently Miss Delacour had come while he
was out in O&apos;Neill&apos;s&quot; (89).

&quot;The fog had begun to chill him and he wondered could he touch Pat in
O&apos;Neill&apos;s. He could not touch him for more than a bob--and a bob was
no use&quot; (92).</description>
