		<Placemark>
			<name>Fownes Street</name>
			<description><![CDATA["Counterparts"<br>[where O'Halloran made his retort to a clerk in an office he was in]<br>"O'Halloran stood tailors of malt, hot, all round and told the story of 
the retort he had made to the chief clerk when he was in Callan's of 
Fownes's Street; but, as the retort was after the manner of the liberal 
shepherds in the eclogues, he had to admit that it was not as clever as 
Farrington's retort" (93).<br>]]></description>
