		<Placemark>
			<name>Nelson&apos;s Pillar</name>
			<description><![CDATA[[one stop along Maria's route]<br>"From Ballsbridge to the Pillar, twenty minutes; from the Pillar to 
Drumcondra, twenty minutes; and twenty minutes to buy the things. She 
would be there before eight" (100)<br>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin00</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.259808,53.349598,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Drumcondra</name>
			<description><![CDATA["Clay" <br>[where Joe lives]<br>"From Ballsbridge to the Pillar, twenty minutes; from the Pillar to 
Drumcondra, twenty minutes; and twenty minutes to buy the things. She 
would be there before eight" (100).<br><br>"She thought she would have to stand in the Drumcondra tram because none 
of the young men seemed to notice her but an elderly gentleman made room
 for her" (102).]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin00</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.262807999999999,53.362385,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Belfast</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<div dir="ltr">&quot;Clay&quot;<br>[where Maria&#39;s purse was purchased]<br>&quot;She took out her purse with the silver clasps and read again the words A Present from Belfast. She was very fond of that purse because Joe had brought it to her five years before when he and Alphy had gone to Belfast on a Whit-Monday trip&quot; (100).</div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin00</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-5.910645,54.591957,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Downes&apos;s Cakeshop</name>
			<description><![CDATA["Clay"<br>[where Maria buys penny cakes]<br>"She went into Downes's cake-shop but the shop was so full of people that
 it was a long time before she could get herself attended to...She decided to buy some plumcake but Downes's plumcake had not enough 
almond icing on top of it so she went over to a shop in Henry Street" (102).<br>]]></description>
