	<Folder>
		<name>&quot;The Dead&quot;</name>
		<description>Streets, Locations, and Routes in &quot;The Dead.&quot;</description>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Stoney Batter</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<div dir="ltr">&quot;The Dead&quot;<br>[the place Kate, Julia, and Mary Jane left after their brother Pat died]<br>&quot;For years and years it had gone off in splendid style, as long as anyone could remember; ever since Kate and Julia, after the death of their brother Pat, had left the house in Stoney Batter and taken Mary Jane, their only niece, to live with them in the dark, gaunt house on Usher&#39;s Island, the upper part of which they had rented from Mr. Fulham, the corn-factor on the ground floor&quot; (176).</div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#msn_ylw-pushpin11</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.282098,53.350693,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Usher&apos;s Island</name>
			<description><![CDATA["The Dead"<br>[where the Misses Morkan live; the setting of the party]<br>"For years and years it had gone off in splendid style, as long as anyone could remember; ever since Kate and Julia, after the death of their brother Pat, had left the house in Stoney Batter and taken Mary Jane, their only niece, to live with them in the dark, gaunt house on Usher's Island, the upper part of which they had rented from Mr. Fulham, the corn-factor on the ground floor" (176).<br>]]></description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>-6.282374664358806</longitude>
				<latitude>53.34598209101767</latitude>
				<altitude>0</altitude>
				<heading>0.0002273054186493474</heading>
				<tilt>0</tilt>
				<range>261.9642004638501</range>
				<gx:altitudeMode>relativeToSeaFloor</gx:altitudeMode>
			</LookAt>
			<styleUrl>#msn_ylw-pushpin11</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.282658,53.346397,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Haddington Road</name>
			<description><![CDATA["The Dead"<br>[where Mary Jane "ha[s] the organ"]<br>"Mary Jane, who was then a little girl in short clothes, was now the main prop of the household, for she had the organ in Haddington Road" (176).<br>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin71</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.239469,53.335758,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Antient Concert Rooms</name>
			<description><![CDATA["The Dead" <br>[where Mary Jane gives pupils' concerts]<br>"She had been through the Academy<br>and gave a pupils' concert every year in the upper room of the Antient<br>Concert Rooms" (176).<br>(address according to Gifford)<br>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin71</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.250073999999999,53.344395,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Kingstown</name>
			<description><![CDATA["The Dead"<br>[one of the areas Mary Jane's students live]<br>"Many of her pupils belonged to the better-class families on the Kingstown and Dalkey line" (176).<br>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#msn_ylw-pushpin11</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.148380359998757,53.29051756535317,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Dalkey</name>
			<description><![CDATA["The Dead"<br>[one of the areas served by the train Mary Jane's students live near]<br>"Many of her pupils belonged to the better-class families on the Kingstown and Dalkey line" (176).<br>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#msn_ylw-pushpin11</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.105697999999999,53.279133,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Adam and Eve&apos;s</name>
			<description><![CDATA["The Dead"<br>[where Julia sings soprano]<br>"Julia, though she was quite grey, was still the leading soprano in Adam and Eve's, and Kate, being too feeble to go about much, gave music lessons to beginners on the old square piano in the back room" (176).<br><br>(According to Gifford, Adam and Eve's was a "[p]opular name for the Franciscan Church of St. Francis of Assisi in Merchant's Quay" [112])<br>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin71</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.274325,53.345119,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Port and Docks</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<div dir="ltr">&quot;The Dead&quot;<br>[where Gabriel&#39;s father worked]<br>&quot;They both kissed Gabriel frankly. He was their favourite nephew the son of their dead elder sister, Ellen, who had married T. J. Conroy of the<br>Port and Docks&quot; (179).</div>]]></description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>-6.217363243720055</longitude>
				<latitude>53.35083974301691</latitude>
				<altitude>0</altitude>
				<heading>0.0008109398037915415</heading>
				<tilt>0</tilt>
				<range>2325.099460714624</range>
				<gx:altitudeMode>relativeToSeaFloor</gx:altitudeMode>
			</LookAt>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin71</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.218374,53.35086800000001,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Monkstown</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<div dir="ltr">&quot;The Dead&quot;<br>[where Gabriel and Gretta live]<br>&quot;--Gretta tells me you&#39;re not going to take a cab back to Monkstown tonight, Gabriel, said Aunt Kate&quot; (180).</div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin71</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.153396,53.293205,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Merrion</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<div dir="ltr">&quot;The Dead&quot;<br>[the point on the Conroys&#39; journey home the previous year after which Gretta got a cold]<br><br>--No, said Gabriel, turning to his wife, we had quite enough of that last year, hadn&#39;t we? Don&#39;t you remember, Aunt Kate, what a cold Gretta got out of it? Cab windows rattling all the way, and the east wind blowing in after we passed Merrion. Very jolly it was. Gretta caught a dreadful cold&quot; (180).</div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin71</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.192168999999999,53.30257,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>The Gresham Hotel Dublin</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<div dir="ltr">&quot;The Dead&quot;<br>[where Gabriel and Gretta stay]<br>&quot;--O, the room is all right, replied Gabriel. I&#39;ve taken one in the<br>Gresham&quot; (181).</div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin71</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.260879,53.35165,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Balbriggan</name>
			<description><![CDATA["The Dead"<br>[where Gabriel's brother is a curate]<br>"Thanks to her, Constantine was now senior curate in Balbrigan and, thanks to her, Gabriel himself had taken his degree in the Royal University" (186).<br>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin71</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.184122,53.607685,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Bachelor&apos;s Walk</name>
			<description><![CDATA["The Dead"<br>[where Gabriel buys books at Hickey's and O'Clohissey's]<br>"Nearly every day when his teaching in the<br>college was ended he used to wander down the quays to the second-hand<br>booksellers, to Hickey's on Bachelor's Walk, to Web's or Massey's on Aston's Quay, or to O'Clohissey's in the bystreet" (188).<br>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin71</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.260034,53.347355,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Aston Quay</name>
			<description><![CDATA["The Dead"<br>[where Gabriel buys books at Web's and Massey's]<br>"Nearly every day when his teaching in the<br>college was ended he used to wander down the quays to the second-hand<br>booksellers, to Hickey's on Bachelor's Walk, to Web's or Massey's on<br>Aston's Quay, or to O'Clohissey's in the bystreet" (188).<br>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin71</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.260016999999999,53.34676,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Aran Isles</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<div dir="ltr">&quot;The Dead&quot;<br>[where Molly Ivors is going for a month-long excursion with Mr Kilkelly and Kathleen Kearney]<br>&quot;--O, Mr. Conroy, will you come for an excursion to the Aran Isles this summer? We&#39;re going to stay there a whole month. It will be splendid out in the Atlantic. You ought to come. Mr. Clancy is coming, and Mr. Kilkelly and Kathleen Kearney. It would be splendid for Gretta too if she&#39;d come. She&#39;s from Connacht, isn&#39;t she?&quot; (188)<br></div>]]></description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>-9.600464767394973</longitude>
				<latitude>53.07358139132354</latitude>
				<altitude>0</altitude>
				<heading>-0.05487388690859411</heading>
				<tilt>0</tilt>
				<range>26510.23223410338</range>
				<gx:altitudeMode>relativeToSeaFloor</gx:altitudeMode>
			</LookAt>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin71</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-9.531841999999999,53.05733099999999,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Connacht</name>
			<description><![CDATA["The Dead"<br>[where Gretta's people are from]<br>"--O, Mr. Conroy, will you come for an excursion to the Aran Isles this summer? We're going to stay there a whole month. It will be splendid out in the Atlantic. You ought to come. Mr. Clancy is coming, and Mr. Kilkelly and Kathleen Kearney. It would be splendid for Gretta too if she'd come. She's from Connacht, isn't she?" (189).<br>]]></description>
			<LookAt>
