			</LookAt>
			<styleUrl>#msn_ylw-pushpin11</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-7.858994443448099,52.18872731654472,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Back Lane</name>
			<description><![CDATA["The Dead"<br>[where the Morkans's "ancestral mansion" was]<br>"--So the old gentleman, as I said, harnessed Johnny and put on his very best tall hat and his very best stock collar and drove out in grand style from his ancestral mansion somewhere near Back<br>Lane, I think.<br><br>Everyone laughed, even Mrs. Malins, at Gabriel's manner and Aunt Kate said:<br><br>--O, now, Gabriel, he didn't live in Back Lane, really. Only the mill was there" (207-08).<br>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin71</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.273225,53.34251399999999,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>College Green</name>
			<description><![CDATA["The Dead"<br>[where the statue of "King Billy" is located]<br>"--Out from the mansion of his forefathers, continued Gabriel, he drove with Johnny. And everything went on beautifully until Johnny came in sight of King Billy's statue: and whether he fell in love with the horse<br>King Billy sits on or whether he thought he was back again in the mill, anyhow he began to walk round the statue" (208).<br>]]></description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>-6.260377853226162</longitude>
				<latitude>53.34427543840698</latitude>
				<altitude>0</altitude>
				<heading>-2.553921581366857e-05</heading>
				<tilt>0</tilt>
				<range>410.6911730552659</range>
