			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.258795,53.344471,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Four Courts</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<div dir="ltr">&quot;The Dead&quot;<br>[a place Gabriel, Gretta, D&#39;Arcy, and Miss O&#39;Callaghan see across the river as they leave the party]<br>&quot;The lamps were still burning redly in the murky air and, across the river, the palace of the Four Courts stood out menacingly against the heavy sky&quot; (213).</div>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin71</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.273685,53.345699,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Winetavern Street</name>
			<description><![CDATA["The Dead"<br>[where Gabriel, Gretta, D'Arcy, and O'Callaghan find the cab]<br>"At the corner of Winetavern Street they met a cab" (214).<br>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin71</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.27212,53.344921,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>O&apos;Connell Street</name>
			<description><![CDATA["The Dead"<br>[where the cab turns and crosses the bridge]<br>"As the cab drove across O'Connell Bridge Miss O'Callaghan said:<br><br>--They say you never cross O'Connell Bridge without seeing a white horse" (214).<br>]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#m_ylw-pushpin71</styleUrl>
			<Point>
				<coordinates>-6.259916,53.348698,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Henry Street</name>
			<description><![CDATA["The Dead"<br>[where Malins had opened a shop]<br>"--O, at Christmas, when he opened that little Christmas-card shop in Henry Street" (217).<br>]]></description>
			<LookAt>
